Appendix A: Training details
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We construct a non-ergodic dataset from 8 Mess3 instances with parameter pairs
\begin_inset Formula $(\alpha,x)\in\{(0.60,0.15),(0.79,0.11),(0.60,0.50),(0.90,0.05),(0.40,0.30),(0.70,0.25),(0.85,0.10),(0.50,0.40)\}$
\end_inset

.
 Each Mess3 instance is a 3-state HMM emitting tokens from
\begin_inset Formula $\{0,1,2\}$
\end_inset

,
 parameterized by
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 (emission peakedness) and
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 (hidden state mixing rate).
 We sample 10,000 sequences of length 16 per instance (80,000 total),
 where each sequence is generated entirely from one ergodic instance.
 The model sees only token sequences: no instance label is provided.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The transformer has 3 layers,
\begin_inset Formula $d_{\text{model}}=64$
\end_inset

,
\begin_inset Formula $d_{\text{MLP}}=256$
\end_inset

,
 4 attention heads,
 and a context window of 16 (151k parameters).
 We train with Adam (
\begin_inset Formula $\text{lr}=3\times10^{-4}$
\end_inset

) for up to 200 epochs with early stopping: we fit a line to
\begin_inset Formula $\log(\text{epoch})$
\end_inset

 vs
\begin_inset Formula $\log(\text{loss})$
\end_inset

 over the last 20 epochs and stop when the slope exceeds
\begin_inset Formula $-0.005$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

