\begin_layout Section*
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:supervised-appendix"

\end_inset

Appendix B: Supervised readout projections
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As a complement to the unsupervised PCA projections used in the main text,
 we here show the same analyses using a supervised linear readout.
 For each layer,
 we fit a Ridge regression from residual stream activations to the ground-truth predictive vectors
\begin_inset Formula $\bm{\eta}^{(x_{1:t})}$
\end_inset

,
 which are computable from the known Mess3 transition matrices.
 For the per-instance plots,
 we fit one readout per instance: for the separation plots,
 we fit a single readout across both instances so the projection space is shared.
 Since the belief states live on a 2-simplex,
 we display the first two coordinates of the predicted belief vector.
\end_layout

